<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-03 00:59 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A5862 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BKC-USC-LADN     01-03 0557
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKC-USC-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BAD START, WILDER FINISH FOR USC
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ It took USC six weeks to build an 8-1
nonconference record, but only 16 minutes of its Pacific-10 opener
to nearly squander the respect it earned from the successful start.
</P>
<P>
   Not even one half into its first league game Saturday night, the
Trojans trailed Arizona State by 18 points, and seemed easy targets
for those claiming they benefited from a soft schedule.
</P>
<P>
   The critics will have to wait a while longer before that
argument sticks, however, because the Trojans mounted a spirited
comeback and defeated the Sun Devils 72-70 before 3,072 at the
Sports Arena.
</P>
<P>
   USC (9-1, 1-0) averted a disaster at the start of Pac-10 play by
outscoring Arizona State 52-32 in the final 24 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   It also took one dramatic defensive stop to assure the victory.
With 8.1 seconds left, the Sun Devils (8-5, 0-1) were in position
to tie or possibly win the game, trailing by two points. But USC
guard Quincy Wilder poked the ball away from Sun Devils guard Eddie
House, and guard Alton Mason traveled during a frantic attempt to
pick up the loose ball and shoot with less than a second remaining.
</P>
<P>
   ``I saw an opportunity when House crossed the ball over to poke
it loose. And I figured with my longer wingspan I could,'' Wilder
said.
</P>
<P>
   USC's comeback was spurred primarily by Wilder, who scored a
career-high 13 points in his best game of the season, and shooting
guard Elias Ayuso, who scored 18 points, including four 3-pointers.
</P>
<P>
   Wilder and Ayuso were the only Trojans in double figures besides
the reliable Brian Scalabrine, who made 10 of 12 shots and had a
game-high 25 points.
</P>
<P>
   ``It didn't look good for a while there,'' USC coach Henry Bibby
said. ``At the beginning, they didn't miss any shots. They made
tough shots, they were knocking shots down. But our defense picked
up when Quincy Wilder and Larry (Elias) Ayuso went into the game
and our intensity picked up.''
</P>
<P>
   The Trojans finally tied the contest 60-60 with 6:18 remaining
when Ayuso hit a 3-pointer. Arizona State pulled ahead 65-62, but
Wilder hit a 3-pointer with 2:30 left, his first of the season, as
the 35-second clock was about to expire.
</P>
<P>
   ``Coach Bibby takes me out of practice if I don't shoot the
ball,'' Wilder said. ``The clock was running down and I really felt
in the flow of the game.''
</P>
<P>
   That was Wilder's biggest play, before his defensive stop at the
end.
</P>
<P>
   ``We've been waiting for our veteran players to pick it up,''
Bibby said. ``We've been waiting for our shooters to pick it up.''
</P>
<P>
   Bibby was referring to Ayuso. The senior guard has slumped this
season, shooting only 32 percent on 3-point attempts. On Saturday,
Bibby benched him for the first time this season. And it worked.
</P>
<P>
   ``The past few games haven't been going well for me. I've been
struggling,'' Ayuso said. ``It did push me a lot, but I kind of
expected (being benched) because I haven't been doing the job. We
need a shooter.''
</P>
<P>
   Notes: USC is off to its best start since 1975-76, when the
Trojans started 11-1.... The Trojans shot a season-high 59.6
percent. Monday's game against Arizona has become a businessman's
special and will tip off at 1 p.m. at the Sports Arena.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-01-03-99 0059EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
