<HEADLINE>
KRAFT IS UNDECIDED ON CARROLL 
</HEADLINE>
  (lb) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   JACKSONVILLE, Fla. _ The New England Patriots' owner, Robert
Kraft, is undecided about whether to keep coach Pete Carroll,
according to a high-ranking team official.
</P>
<P>
   In their 25-10 loss to the Jaguars on Sunday in an American
Football Conference playoff game, the Patriots were plagued by
problems that they have faced all year, including injuries and a
lack of discipline on the field.
</P>
<P>
   There is also some question whether Carroll has the full support
of the players. Some said privately after Sunday's loss that
Carroll needed to be more of a disciplinarian.
</P>
<P>
   Kraft would not discuss in detail his thoughts on whether he
would keep Carroll, though he said the high number of key Patriot
injuries should be a factor in any decision about the coach's
future.
</P>
<P>
   Kraft added that Carroll and his staff would be evaluated in the
coming days.
</P>
</TEXT>
