<P>
   &UR; IS INTERNET KILLING ENGLISH LANGUAGE _ AND CIVILITY? &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (ATTN: Commentary Editors) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   By Andrew Gumbel &QL;
</P>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO _ ``Flaming'' _ an e-mail phenomenon characterized
by an outbreak of insults and tantrums of a kind that seems
particularly common online _ is only one peculiarity that the
Internet appears to have brought to the English language.
</P>
<P>
   According to various researchers, the Internet may also be
eroding the formal structure of the language, introducing errors of
grammar and spelling and making them acceptable, and winnowing away
at the overall complexity of English _ in other words, dumbing it
down. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (775 words) &QL;
</P>
