<HEADLINE>
MEMO TO NBA: DROP DEAD
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Here's the final proposal from us, da fan, as we
view this half-cocked idea of making Thursday the do-or-die date
for playing half an NBA season _ which is as typically presumptuous
as a Michael Jordan comeback:
</P>
<P>
   Owners, you stick with your demands.
</P>
<P>
   Players, you stick with your dreams.
</P>
<P>
   Thursday, we decide it with a free throw _ taken by Shaquille
O'Neal.
</P>
<P>
   He makes it, go with the players' deal.
</P>
<P>
   He misses, go with the owners' deal.
</P>
<P>
   Of course, we can't get the players to agree to that, so...
</P>
<P>
   In that case, pull the plug. The damage is irreversible and
we're out of patience....
</P>
<P>
   _Results from an ESPN.com Internet poll asking ``With David
Stern's `drop dead' date coming, do you think there will be a
season?'' Almost 60 percent of the 14,438 voters responded ``Don't
care.''...
</P>
<P>
   _Michael Olowokandi's threats to play in Italy are no baloney.
If the Kinder Bologna team signs him today, as reported, the
Clippers can't stop him, they can only hope to contain him....
</P>
<P>
   _Kareem Abdul-Jabbar could be the Clippers' coach by the time
they move into the Staples Center....
</P>
<P>
   _NHL vice president of communications Bernadette Mansur, on why
the league doesn't market itself more to get those NBA fans who
have nothing to watch: ``We don't have the same demographics as NBA
fans. Our (fans) are more affluent and educated.''...
</P>
<P>
   _The Dodgers have sent out letters inviting folks to one of two
90-minute Q-and-A gatherings _ with a Stadium Club hot-dog buffet _
they have set up with manager Davey Johnson, CEO Bob Graziano and
GM Kevin Malone to ``discuss our vision for the 1999 Dodger team.''
One of the meetings is next Monday _ show up at 10 a.m. and see the
usually no-fans-allowed players' winter workouts at Dodger Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   Oh, wait a sec. These invites are only for the Dodgers'
preferred season-ticket holders from the dugout, field and loge
levels. Sorry, bleacher scums....
</P>
<P>
   _This should be the year when the arrogant-for-no-reason
baseball writers allow Nolan Ryan, George Brett, Robin Yount,
Carlton Fisk (begin ital)and(end ital) Tony Perez into C'town's
pearly gates. When Tuesday's ballots are made public, though, don't
be stunned when only Ryan and Brett get their hands stamped....
</P>
<P>
   _John Madden calls Sunday's San Fran-Green Bay playoff game
``one of the greatest we've ever seen.'' Duh....
</P>
<P>
   _And the ball is still loose from Jerry Rice's fumble....
</P>
<P>
   _Sugar Bowl halftime entertainment act Roger Staubach put up
better stats than Troy Aikman_ did in that NFC mild-card effort....
</P>
<P>
   _The next proposed adjustment to the Rube Goldberg-looking Bowl
Championship Non-Series is adding a fifth category to determining
the rankings _ the margin of victory against Top 25 opponents. One
that Steve ``I'm Giving Myself The Game Ball'' Spurrier fully
endorses....
</P>
<P>
   _It would make sense if Chris Claiborne, R. Jay Soward and Kris
Farris jump to the NFL _ and avoid the embarrassment of walking
around campus after what happened last week....
</P>
<P>
   _Trojans teammates were grumbling that Claiborne, who helped USC
hold Texas Christian to just 314 yards rushing, musta gained about
30 extra pounds from the banquet circuit between the end of the
regular season and the Sun Bowl....
</P>
<P>
   _If Farris wanted to come up with a movie title to describe the
Rose Bowl, it could be ``Farris' Bruins' Day Off.''...
</P>
<P>
   _For a change, USC's switch to a 1 p.m. tipoff for today's
basketball game against Arizona has nothing to do with a conflict
over a birthday party previously planned for a coach's wife. Why
UCLA didn't adjust its tipoff with Arizona State _ it'll go up
against the Pseudo Bowl between Tennessee and Florida State in
ASU's Sun Devil Stadium _ doesn't make much sense. &QL; 
Tom Hoffarth can be reached at sptmediaaol.com or (818) 713-3661.
</P>
</TEXT>
