<P>
   (NYT11) NEW YORK -- Jan. 3, 1999 -- 1999-COHEN, 1-3 -- Abby
Joseph Cohen, the chief investment strategist at Goldman, Sachs &AMP;
Co., did not flinch in August when the stock market sank. Instead,
Cohen telephoned her clients and told them the same thing she told
them a year earlier when the market seemed to be in free fall:
``Stay the course.'' ``When we do a retrospective of 1999 we'll be
saying, 'It wasn't so bad after all,''' says Cohen. (Angel
Franco/New York Times Photo)
</P>
