Michael Gruber, a prestigious neuro-oncologist from the University
of California in Los Angeles, was recruited by New York University
to run the NYU Medical Center neuro-oncology unit. ``Cancer is to
the 1990s what heart disease was to the 1970s,'' says Gruber. ``It
puts a center on the map, and that begets business.'' (Ruby
Washington/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT8) UNDATED -- Jan. 3, 1999 -- REPUBS-POLITICS, 1-3 -- With a
stick in one hand, a water bottle in the other and no gavel in
sight, Rep. Newt Gingrich, the outgoing House Speaker, climbing
Camelback Mountain near Phoenix Sunday during a Republican retreat.
Gingrich spoke Saturday night at a banquet that concluded an annual
New Year's conference of about 300 conservatives called The Weekend
but known as the Dark Ages. (Jeff Topping/New York Times Photo)
</P>
