   &UR; NATIONAL _ GENERAL (Moved in ``a'' category) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   NY-CANCER-COMPETE (New York) _ Cancer is hot in New York, and,
across the city, the major medical centers are aggressively
attempting to nibble away at Memorial Sloan-Kettering's market
share. (Sloan-Kettering was always the place to go for cancer
treatment in New York, because of its prestigious doctors, esteemed
reputation for clinical research and the promising drugs trials it
conducts.) While the concentration on cancer is a nationwide
phenomenon, experts say the new competition is particularly fevered
in New York, where there are already more centers that have the
official designation of the National Cancer Institute _ and its
funding _ than in most other regions.
</P>
<P>
   ST.CROIX-CASINO (St. Croix, U.S.V.I.) _ St. Croix's first casino
is scheduled to open here this fall. In a region battered by four
major hurricanes in the last decade, casinos are seen as a catalyst
to help bring back the economic prosperity that all but vanished in
September 1989, when Hurricane Hugo left 90 percent of the
buildings damaged and more than 20,000 people homeless. By Mireya
Navarro.
